 1. Executive Summary
This document presents a complete Proof of Concept for the Pet IoT Analytics Platform — an end-to-end cloud data engineering pipeline built on Microsoft Azure. The project demonstrates the full lifecycle of IoT data from synthetic generation through ingestion, transformation, governance, and analytical consumption by three distinct business audiences.

The platform ingests data from 10,000 simulated IoT pet devices owned by 5,000 pet owners across 10 countries. Device data covers GPS tracking, health monitoring, smart feeding, hydration monitoring, firmware deployments, and device failures. The pipeline processes this data through a Medallion Architecture (Raw → Bronze → Silver → Gold) using Azure Data Factory for orchestration, Azure Databricks with PySpark for processing, Delta Lake for ACID-compliant storage, Unity Catalog for governance, and Power BI for dashboard delivery.

