 2. Project Overview & Business Context
2.1 Problem Statement
A pet technology company manufactures and sells IoT devices for pets including GPS collars, health monitors, smart feeders, water fountains, pet cameras, and automated litter systems. The company collects continuous telemetry from 10,000 active devices but has no unified data platform to answer key business questions:
•	Are devices from specific factories failing more than others?
•	Is firmware update success rate declining across device generations?
•	Which pets are showing abnormal health patterns over time?
•	Which sales channels generate the highest net revenue?
•	Are smart feeder devices dispensing correct food portions consistently?

2.2 Proposed Solution
Build a cloud-native data platform on Microsoft Azure using the Medallion Architecture. Raw IoT device telemetry lands in Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2, is processed through three transformation layers (Bronze, Silver, Gold) using Azure Databricks and Delta Lake, governed through Unity Catalog, and delivered to three tailored Power BI dashboards for Pet Owners, Manufacturers, and the Sales Executive Team.

