  5. Data Model — Star Schema
5.1 Schema Design Decisions
The data model follows a classic star schema with 6 dimension tables (describing entities) and 8 fact tables (recording events and measurements). All dimension tables use a single primary key. Fact tables use either a single surrogate key or a composite natural key (device_id + timestamp for snapshot tables).

Q: Why use a star schema rather than a normalised 3NF model?
A: Star schemas are optimised for analytical query patterns — BI tools like Power BI generate simpler SQL with fewer joins against star schemas compared to normalised models. Dimensional models also support partitioning and ZORDER optimisation in Delta Lake more effectively, since query predicates typically filter on fact table date columns and join to dimensions by key.

