Q: How does the parameter flow from the trigger all the way to the Databricks notebook?
A: TRG_Daily_Bronze fires with window_start_time = @trigger().outputs.windowStartTime (e.g. "2025-01-03T00:00:00Z"). This passes to PL_Master_MDR_Orchestrator as a string parameter. The Master's ExecutePipeline activities forward it to PL_Ingest_Raw_To_Bronze using the Expression type: @pipeline().parameters.window_start_time. Inside the Bronze pipeline, the Notebook Activity's base parameter p_load_date is set to: @if(empty(pipeline().parameters.window_start_time), formatDateTime(utcNow(),"yyyy-MM-dd"), formatDateTime(pipeline().parameters.window_start_time,"yyyy-MM-dd")). This evaluated string (e.g. "2025-01-03") is received by the Databricks notebook via dbutils.widgets.get("load_date").

