Q: Why use a Tumbling Window trigger rather than a Schedule trigger?
A: A Tumbling Window trigger maintains state — it tracks exactly which windows have succeeded and which are pending. When the trigger starts with startTime=2021-01-01, ADF automatically generates every missing daily window from 2021-01-01 to the current date, effectively running a backfill. A Schedule trigger has no memory of historical runs and cannot backfill. Additionally, Tumbling Window makes the window boundaries (windowStartTime, windowEndTime) available as trigger output variables, which we pass directly as the pipeline's load_date parameter.

