  12. Gold Layer Notebooks
12.1 Design Philosophy & Staged Join Strategy
Gold tables are pre-aggregated for Power BI consumption. The critical design rule is: ALWAYS aggregate fact tables BEFORE joining to dimension tables. Joining a raw 7-million-row fact table to a dimension causes unpredictable row count explosion (fan-out). The staged join pattern avoids this.
Stage 1: Aggregate each fact table independently
  activity_snapshots → group by (pet_id, date) → agg_activity (one row per pet per day)
  health_snapshots   → group by (pet_id, date) → agg_health
  feeding_events     → group by (pet_id, date) → agg_feeding
  hydration_events   → group by (pet_id, date) → agg_hydration
 
Stage 2: Full outer join small aggregates to each other
  agg_activity.join(agg_health, ["pet_id","date"], "full_outer")
              .join(agg_feeding, ["pet_id","date"], "left")
              .join(agg_hydration, ["pet_id","date"], "left")
 
  full_outer is critical: a pet with activity data but no hydration on a given day
  must NOT be dropped. An inner join would silently lose entire days.
 
Stage 3: Enrich with slim dimension joins
  .join(pets_slim, "pet_id", "left")    # add pet_name, species
  .join(owners_slim, "owner_id", "left") # add owner_name, city, country

