13. Audit Framework
13.1 Audit Design
Three Delta tables in the audit/ container capture pipeline-level, table-level, and data-quality-level events. Every orchestrator notebook is integrated with exactly 4 new lines — 2 at the top (start logging) and 2 at the bottom (end logging). No existing notebook logic is modified.
Delta Table	Grain	Key Columns
audit/pipeline_runs	One row per pipeline execution	run_id, pipeline_name, status, start_time, end_time, duration_seconds, load_date
audit/table_runs	One row per table per layer per run	run_id, table_name, layer, status, input_rows, output_rows, rows_dropped, duration_seconds
audit/data_quality	One row per fact table per Silver run	run_id, table_name, null_rows_found, duplicate_rows_found, out_of_range_rows_found, anomaly_rate_pct, dq_status

