19. Conclusions & Learnings
What Was Demonstrated
•	End-to-end data engineering pipeline from synthetic generation to Power BI dashboards on Microsoft Azure
•	Medallion Architecture (Raw → Bronze → Silver → Gold) with Delta Lake throughout
•	Modular, testable notebook architecture with strict single-responsibility separation (20 notebooks, each with one job)
•	Referential integrity enforced programmatically across 14 tables from generation through all pipeline layers
•	Incremental load via Tumbling Window trigger, Auto Loader checkpoint, and day-partitioned raw storage
•	Data quality pipeline: 5% controlled anomaly injection + 24 specific cleaning rules in Silver + DQ audit
•	Unity Catalog governance with managed Gold tables queryable by Power BI
•	Audit framework with 3 Delta tables and 9 pre-built query patterns

Key Technical Decisions
Decision	Outcome
All-StringType schema at Bronze	Zero Bronze load failures regardless of anomaly injection. Silver owns all type casting.
cloudFiles.schemaEvolutionMode removed	Resolved incompatibility with explicit schema on DBR 13.3. schema_manager handles evolution.
saveAsTable vs LOCATION for Gold	Bypassed External Location IAM blocker. Managed UC tables work identically for Power BI.
Full outer join between fact aggregates	Prevented silent loss of pets with partial device coverage (e.g. has collar but no health monitor)
availableNow=True for streaming write	Converts Auto Loader stream to batch-like behaviour — processes queue then terminates cleanly
New Job Cluster in ADF Linked Service	Eliminated driver crash under concurrent load. Each notebook execution gets isolated compute.
_load_date lineage column for Silver filter	Simpler than watermark table — Bronze injects date, Silver reads it. No write contention.

Learnings
•	ADF parameter expressions require "Add dynamic content" button, not just typing @expression text in a plain field
•	Tumbling Window backfill requires startTime set to earliest data date, not today — otherwise historical partitions are never processed
•	Interactive clusters are not appropriate for unattended ADF pipeline workloads with multiple concurrent executions
•	Unity Catalog External Location requires explicit IAM role assignment on the target storage account — storage firewall or missing role both silently block it
•	Power BI Import mode is always preferred for aggregated Gold tables — DirectQuery only needed when tables exceed 1GB or real-time freshness is required
